### Document Summary

This document is an "IBM Batch Report" for Electoral Event ID 19694 (Senate) in NSW, specifically for Vote Collection Point "Bangor" (ID 2178), Batch Number 10. It was created on June 10, 2016, with a report date of June 15, 2016. The report details the processing outcomes for 54 individual ballots within this batch, identified by Ballot Number and Ballot ID. For each ballot, it records the results of various checks including Quality Assurance, Initials, Official Mark, Unusual Markings, Formality Result, Verification Action, Formality Reason, and all Above-the-Line (ATL) and Below-the-Line (BTL) preference checks (Preferences, Mismatches, Saved, Breakdown, Formal). All 54 ballots listed in this report show an "OK" status across all checked categories, indicating successful processing without detected anomalies for these specific entries.

### Relevance to FOI Request

This document is directly relevant to Vanessa Teague's FOI request [LEX540] for 'IBM Outputs' from 2016, as it is one of the "IBM Batch Report" PDF files dated June 10 and 15, 2016. It provides the specific ballot-level processing details, including batch metadata, electoral event context, and the comprehensive set of checks for formality, initials, marks, and preferences (ATL/BTL) that the FOI request aims to uncover. While the FOI overview notes that various checks (e.g., `UnusualMarkings Checked`, `Verification Action`, `ATL Mismatches`, `BTL Mismatches`) frequently show "HAS ISSUES" entries, this particular report serves as an example of a batch where all recorded checks for the processed ballots yielded "OK" results, providing a baseline of successful processing within the broader context of the request for insights into ballot handling and anomaly detection.
